    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of what I found and the implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` Subcommand\n\n### What I explored\n\n- **`CacheCommand` enum** (`uv-cli/src/lib.rs`, ~line 879): has `Clean`, `Prune`, `Dir`, `Size(SizeArgs)` — I'll add `Stats(StatsArgs)` after `Size`\n- **`SizeArgs` struct** (~line 948): single `human: bool` field — `StatsArgs` will be identical in structure\n- **`cache_size.rs`**: uses `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` for size calculation; has a `preview` gate — **`cache_stats` will NOT need this gate**\n- **`CacheBucket::iter()`** (`uv-cache/src/lib.rs`, line 1316): yields 10 buckets (Wheels, SourceDistributions, FlatIndex, Git, Interpreter, Simple, Archive, Builds, Environments, Binaries — notably excludes `Python`)\n- **`Cache::bucket()`** (line 281): returns `PathBuf` = `cache.root.join(bucket.to_str())`\n- **`CacheBucket::Display`**: delegates to `to_str()` → versioned names like `wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`\n- **Dispatch pattern** (`uv/src/lib.rs`, line 1179): simple match arm calling `commands::cache_size(&cache, args.human, printer, globals.preview)`\n\n### 4 changes required\n\n| # | File | Change |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` | Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` + define `StatsArgs` struct |\n| 2 | `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` | New file: iterate `CacheBucket::iter()`, measure each bucket with `DiskUsage`, print per-bucket + total |\n| 3 | `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs` | Add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` |\n| 4 | `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` | Add dispatch arm `CacheCommand::Stats(args) => commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` |",
